OL,4,Cfootfall in early August
OL,6,FThis meant that the footfall decline
OL,7,Foverall in the month still improved
OL,8,Fdespite the riots, paring back from a
OL,9,F3.3% decline in July.
OL,11,FThe data also showed that Northern
OL,12,FIreland and Scotland enjoyed a rise in
OL,13,Fshopper footfall, up 1.4% and 0.7%
OL,14,Fyear-on-year respectively, while there
OL,15,Fwere declines of 0.5% across England
OL,16,Fand 1.8% in Wales.
